1
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:06,400
Grandview welcomes home town hero
SGT.Matt Murphy

2
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:09,600
look at this.

3
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:11,700
The whole town wants to welcome him back,

4
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:13,300
and he comes home in the middle of the night.

5
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,800
Well, maybe he doesn't want all the attention.

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,700
Hey, the guy got the silver star.
He should bask in the glory.

7
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,900
Poor guy probably won't get a moment's peace.

8
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,300
I'm just glad my buddy is back safe.

9
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:25,200
You think he's gonna be different?

10
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,900
I think two tours in iraq would change anybody,

11
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,200
but if he just takes it slow,
gets used to being home,

12
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:32,800
and doesn't come back to the firehouse
until he's absolutely ready,

13
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,000
he's gonna be fine.

14
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:55,100
- Matty.
- Hey, hey.

15
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,400
- Welcome home, man.
- How are you, man?

16
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,600
Let me take that for you.

17
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:01,800
- We are so glad that you're back.
- Oh, it's great to be back.

18
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,400
I swear, it's like I've never been away.

19
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:06,500
Everything is just the same.

20
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:16,900
I'm sorry I kept you waiting, babe.

21
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,600
What's a few years between friends?

22
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:21,000
I'm back, baby. I'm yours.

23
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,300
Hey, matt murphy, is that you?

24
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:33,900
Yo, it's matt murphy.
How you doing, man?

25
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,100
I'm good, man. I'm good. How are you?

26
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:37,100
- Good to see you. Doing great.
- Great to see you, too.

27
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:39,100
- Great to see you again.
- All right, guys.

28
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:41,500
Guys, there'll be time to elect
him pope over the weekend, ok,

29
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:44,400
but come to the party, if you can.
Let's get out of here.Let's take him home.

30
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,400
- See you.
- Bye.Take it easy.

31
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,600
Man, I'm sorry to tear you away from your friends.

32
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:51,800
Were you worrying them, too?

33
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:53,600
Hey, come on. Give me a break.

34
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:55,200
Hey, let's go and get a beer, ok?

35
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:57,600
They want to go home.
They don't want company.

36
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:02,400
- Did you hear that?
- Yeah.

37
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:08,500
Well, maybe it was just a car backfiring
or something.

38
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Right.

39
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:14,000
So, your place tomorrow.
What do you want us to bring?

40
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,800
- Matt.
- Matt.

41
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,600
Matt, what is this?

42
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,700
You all right?

43
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,200
Hey...

44
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:34,800
Wow, I--I guess I'm still a little jumpy.

45
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:37,600
- It's ok.
- Let's get you home, ok?

46
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,500
- Yeah. We'll see you guys tomorrow.
- Ok.

47
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:43,800
- Yeah.Early, right?
- Right, first thing.

48
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,600
- Good night.
- Good night.

49
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,900
What just happened there?

50
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:56,200
Haunting of some kind, a very noisy one,
but no one should have heard that but me.

51
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,300
Right. What does that mean?

52
00:02:58,500 --> 00:02:59,700
I don't know,

53
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:04,000
but I think matt brought the war home with him.

54
