00:29:06,200 --> 00:29:09,000
Hector would want it. Please trust me.

479
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:11,700
Since when do you speak for my son?

480
00:29:11,900 --> 00:29:15,400
Now, everything they sent me of his
is locked up out back in storage room.

481
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:17,900
Anna is not ready to look through it.

482
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,800
You know, is anna home?
Because maybe we--

483
00:29:19,900 --> 00:29:24,200
anna took sari to the store.
She was a nervous wreck when I got home.

484
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:26,300
I want you to stay away from her.

485
00:29:28,300 --> 00:29:30,900
Hey! Hey!

486
00:29:33,100 --> 00:29:35,800
Are you nuts? Do I have to call the cops?

487
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,800
It's hot.

488
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:55,500
How is that possible?

489
00:29:55,600 --> 00:29:59,500
Please trust me when I say this.

490
00:30:00,100 --> 00:30:03,600
I think your son wants you
to find what matt gave to him.

491
00:30:28,300 --> 00:30:30,500
This is all I have left of my son.

492
00:30:34,300 --> 00:30:36,900
I said that anna wasn't ready to look through it.

493
00:30:38,500 --> 00:30:40,800
It's really me who isn'T.

494
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:47,300
I keep thinking that if I don't open the box,

495
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:51,000
it's like it's not really final.

496
00:30:53,500 --> 00:30:56,000
I won't see the end of my son.

497
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:59,400
I am so sorry.

498
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,900
My jacket--

499
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:28,500
my right vest pocket.

500
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:34,700
Maybe you should check his jacket--
right vest pocket.

501
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:02,900
I wasn't afraid, dad.
I know I wasn'T.

502
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:07,000
Told me how to be tough, and I was.

503
00:32:08,300 --> 00:32:11,100
You should know he wasn't afraid.

504
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:14,800
He was tough, just like you taught him to be.

505
00:32:26,900 --> 00:32:29,600
I don't understand any of this.

506
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:39,900
"Until I get home!"

507
00:32:47,900 --> 00:32:49,900
Is this what you're looking for?

508
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:58,100
What does this all mean?

509
00:32:59,300 --> 00:33:03,000
- Matt. He needs us right now.
- Where?

510
00:33:03,100 --> 00:33:05,000
Where the names are in the village square.

511
00:33:06,500 --> 00:33:09,400
Can I keep this?

512
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:11,900
yeah

513
00:33:19,300 --> 00:33:23,200
Come on. You remember when you were a rookie.

514
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:25,300
You were as green as this grass here,

515
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:31,000
but you plucked me off that fire escape
without a second thought.You saved me,

516
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:34,600
and that wall came crashing down.
I remember, you didn't even blink.

517
00:33:36,900 --> 00:33:39,900
I don't know who that guy was,
but it wasn't me.

518
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:47,400
It wasn't the guy who let his patrol die
in some bombed-out square in iraq.

519
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:51,500
You saw ityo .U know.

520
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:55,800
I don't care what I saw
or what I didn't see on that videotape.

521
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:58,300
I know who you are.

522
00:33:59,300 --> 00:34:01,800
This whole town knows who you are.

523
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:06,300
Nice try, pal.

524
00:34:07,600 --> 00:34:10,100
I appreciate it. I really do.

525
00:34:10,900 --> 00:34:13,300
This isn't about who I am.

526
00:34:14,900 --> 00:34:17,700
It's about what I am.

527
00:34:22,900 --> 00:34:24,400
Matt, what are you doing here?

528
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:26,300
What do you want?

529
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,700
You know what I want, jim?

530
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:39,100
I want to know why I left my men behind.

531
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,600
I want to know why I can't remember what I did

532
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:45,300
and why I keep doing this.

533
00:34:46,200 --> 00:34:48,400
Most of all,

534
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:52,700
I want to know why they're dead and I'm not.

535
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:59,100
Matt, I went to hector's house.
We found this.

536
00:35:00,300 --> 00:35:03,600
You gave it to him
right before you got in the humvee.

537
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:05,800
What does it mean?

538
00:35:16,300 --> 00:35:20,800
You know,these reeds
grow everywhere in the south of baghdad.

539
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:28,600
One day, I was just playing with them,
and I made this.

540
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:33,600
- That's a ring?
- An engagement ring.

541
00:35:34,300 --> 00:35:38,700
It was supposed to be a placeholder
till I could get her a real one.

542
00:35:39,300 --> 00:35:40,500
Why'd you give it to hector?

543
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:43,800
Because he thought he was
one a one-way trip in the humvee.

544
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:46,900
You thought you weren't coming home.

545
00:35:47,100 --> 00:35:50,700
That day that you got in the humvee,
you weren't running scared, were you?

546
00:35:51,500 --> 00:35:54,000
You were on a suicide mission for your men.

547
00:35:54,100 --> 00:35:55,400
How'd you know that?

548
00:35:55,500 --> 00:35:57,000
Hector,

549
00:35:57,500 --> 00:36:02,400
your men, they're here with you,
with us right now.

550
00:36:07,200 --> 00:36:09,400
Rocky?

551
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:14,200
Why?

552
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:17,000
Because we don't leave a man behind,

553
00:36:17,100 --> 00:36:19,900
especially when he never left us.

554
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:23,700
They said you never left them.

555
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,300
What happened?

556
00:36:27,500 --> 00:36:32,100
We got separated from our convoy,
pinned down in that square.

557
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:35,600
He radioed for air cover.
There just wasn't enough time.

558
00:36:35,700 --> 00:36:37,500
get down!get down!

559
00:36:38,300 --> 00:36:41,900
- Where's the fire coming from?
- Storefront across the street, sarge.

560
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,500
We got another one,11 o'clock.

561
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:47,500
Rocky, the gun nest behind that wall--
2, maybe 3 shooters.

562
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:49,800
Can't move.
What are we gonna do?

563
00:37:04,700 --> 00:37:06,100
What are you doing, man?

564
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,600
- You'll know what to do.
- What?

565
00:37:08,700 --> 00:37:11,100
Sarge. Matt,get down, man.

566
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:12,600
- Stop it!
- Let me go!

567
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:13,800
Someone stop him!

568
00:37:13,900 --> 00:37:17,900
Kept trying to pull you back.
You just kept saying,"let me go."

569
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:19,600
I remember.

570
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:24,600
I couldn't take the time to explain it
because if I did--

571
00:37:24,700 --> 00:37:26,700
we wouldn't have let you go.

572
00:37:27,200 --> 00:37:29,900
- Stop murphy!What's that crazy bastard doing?
- Matt!

573
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:31,700
I knew they were confused.

574
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:35,200
All I could do was say a prayer that I'd
make it to the humvee without getting killed.

575
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:36,700
Sarge!

576
00:37:45,500 --> 00:37:50,200
He drove straight into enemy fire.
He was sacrificing himself to save us.

577
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:59,200
Two jihadis left. I got the first one.

578
00:38:00,100 --> 00:38:02,700
Then my gun just jammed.

579
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:06,200
That's why you keep breaking it down
and putting it back together again.

580
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:08,200
Yousre ju't trying to unjam it.

581
00:38:08,300 --> 00:38:11,400
Fall in. Stack on me.
Let's go. Let's get sarge.Go, go, go.

582
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:16,100
Yeah. Yeah. I mean, that was it.

583
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:20,300
My ticket was about to
be punched by the last gunman.

584
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:34,700
And then hector took out the last shooter.

585
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:37,200
You know, we came to save him.

586
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:46,500
They were coming to rescue you.

587
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:52,100
NO!!!

588
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:58,600
But they never made it.
Couldn't accept it.

589
00:38:58,700 --> 00:39:04,300
It was like a part of my brain just shut down.

590
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:08,600
Should've left me.

591
00:39:10,700 --> 00:39:13,900
It should've been 4 survivors and 1 casualty
instead of the other way round.

592
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:15,700
He saved us.

593
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:18,800
There was no way we were leaving without him.

594
00:39:19,900 --> 00:39:23,200
The rest of it?Nobody had any control over
what happened next.

595
00:39:23,300 --> 00:39:27,100
I would've done anything for them,anything.

596
00:39:27,900 --> 00:39:30,300
I'd trade places with them in a heartbeat.

597
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:32,300
You tell matt that he's alive for a reason

598
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:34,800
and that he shouldn't waste
it feeling guilty about us.

599
00:39:34,900 --> 00:39:39,900
Everything that happened was meant to happen.

600
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:44,800
Hector wants you to stop blaming yourself.

601
00:39:44,900 --> 00:39:50,200
You did everything you could.
Everything happens for a reason.

602
00:39:51,500 --> 00:39:54,900
Whoa, that's bright.
Is that a chopper?

603
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:58,800
No. No. That's not a searchlight.

604
00:39:59,700 --> 00:40:01,200
It's beautiful.

605
00:40:01,300 --> 00:40:03,300
What does it mean?

606
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:06,200
It means you're ready to go.

607
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:10,800
Tell anna I love her.

608
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:15,300
Tell her not to let my little girl
forget about her dad.

609
00:40:16,300 --> 00:40:18,200
I will.

610
00:40:18,700 --> 00:40:21,000
Talk to my father.

611
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:23,100
Ask him if he thinks matt didn't try to save us,

612
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:26,100
then why are there bullet holes
in the front grill of our humvee?

613
00:40:27,300 --> 00:40:30,900
It's because matt was going towards the bullets,
not away from them.

614
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:35,400
You tell him that
I want him to watch out for matt now

615
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:38,200
the way matt watched out for me.

616
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:42,900
He's the one that's gonna need help now.

617
00:40:45,100 --> 00:40:46,700
What's happening?

618
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:50,600
They did what they came here to do.

619
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:54,000
They said good-bye.

620
00:41:16,900 --> 00:41:19,400
I've been looking everywhere for you.

621
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:22,500
Sorry.

622
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:25,600
Don't ever leave me again.

623
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:29,800
What part of "I love you" don't you get?

624
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:37,000
- I'm with you.
- I know.

625
00:41:48,100 --> 00:41:50,700
This is all I can give you right now.

626
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:57,300
Now, we'll replace it when we--

627
00:41:57,400 --> 00:42:00,000
don't you dare.

